The Department of Energy has officially detailed the reported decline in the price of fuel that will come into effect from midnight on November sixth.
Attributed to a stronger Rand relative to the US Dollar and weaker international oil prices, the Department has announced that the price of all grades of petrol will drop by 13 cents per litre, diesel by between 14 and 16 cents per litre and illuminating paraffin by 23 cents.
